#: src/providers/fallback-and-routing.md:1
msgid "Fallback & Routing"
msgstr "Fallback y enrutamiento"

#: src/providers/fallback-and-routing.md:3
msgid ""
"Two meta-providers let you stack concrete providers into reliability "
"pipelines and task-aware routing."
msgstr "Dos meta-proveedores te permiten apilar proveedores concretos en pipelines de confiabilidad y enrutamiento consciente de las tareas."

#: src/providers/fallback-and-routing.md:5
msgid "Fallback chains — `reliable`"
msgstr "Cadenas de respaldo — `reliable`"

#: src/providers/fallback-and-routing.md:7
msgid ""
"A `reliable` provider wraps a list of other providers. On timeout, network "
"error, or authentication failure on the first, it transparently falls "
"through to the next."
msgstr "Un proveedor `reliable` envuelve una lista de otros proveedores. En caso de tiempo de espera, error de red o fallo de autenticación en el primero, pasa transparentemente al siguiente."

#: src/providers/fallback-and-routing.md:9
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[providers.models.primary]\n"
"kind = \"reliable\"\n"
"fallback_providers = [\"claude\", \"haiku\", \"local\"]\n"
"# fallback_providers references other [providers.models.*] by name\n"
"\n"
"[providers.models.claude]\n"
"kind = \"anthropic\"\n"
"model = \"claude-sonnet-4-6\"\n"
"api_key = \"sk-ant-...\"\n"
"\n"
"[providers.models.haiku]\n"
"kind = \"anthropic\"\n"
"model = \"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\"\n"
"api_key = \"sk-ant-...\"\n"
"\n"
"[providers.models.local]\n"
"kind = \"ollama\"\n"
"base_url = \"http://localhost:11434\"\n"
"model = \"qwen3.6:35b-a3b\"\n"
"```"
msgstr "```toml\n[providers.models.primary]\nkind = \"reliable\"\nfallback_providers = [\"claude\", \"haiku\", \"local\"]\n# fallback_providers hace referencia a otros [providers.models.*] por nombre\n\n[providers.models.claude]\nkind = \"anthropic\"\nmodel = \"claude-sonnet-4-6\"\napi_key = \"sk-ant-...\"\n\n[providers.models.haiku]\nkind = \"anthropic\"\nmodel = \"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\"\napi_key = \"sk-ant-...\"\n\n[providers.models.local]\nkind = \"ollama\"\nbase_url = \"http://localhost:11434\"\nmodel = \"qwen3.6:35b-a3b\"\n```"

#: src/providers/fallback-and-routing.md:31
msgid "Then:"
msgstr "Luego:"

#: src/providers/fallback-and-routing.md:33
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"default_model = \"primary\"\n"
"```"
msgstr "```toml\nmodelo_predeterminado = \"primary\"\n```"

#: src/providers/fallback-and-routing.md:37
msgid "Behaviour:"
msgstr "Comportamiento:"

#: src/providers/fallback-and-routing.md:39
msgid ""
"Tries `claude` first; on transient error retries twice with exponential "
"backoff (2 s, 4 s)."
msgstr "Intenta primero con `claude`; en caso de error transitorio, reintenta dos veces con retroceso exponencial (2 s, 4 s)."

#: src/providers/fallback-and-routing.md:40
msgid ""
"After two retries exhausted, falls through to `haiku` and restarts the retry "
"cycle."
msgstr "Después de agotar dos reintentos, pasa a `haiku` y reinicia el ciclo de reintentos."

#: src/providers/fallback-and-routing.md:41
msgid "If `haiku` also exhausts, falls through to `local`."
msgstr "Si `haiku` también se agota, pasa a `local`."

#: src/providers/fallback-and-routing.md:42
msgid "Only returns an error once every provider in the chain has failed."
msgstr "Solo devuelve un error una vez que todos los proveedores en la cadena han fallado."

#: src/providers/fallback-and-routing.md:44
msgid ""
"**Best practice — order by reliability:** put the most reliable provider "
"first, not the best. A Claude fallback behind a flaky local Ollama won't "
"save you during an API outage. `[fastest/best_quality, fallback_quality, "
"always_on_local]` is a common pattern."
msgstr "**Mejor práctica — ordenar por fiabilidad:** coloca primero al proveedor más fiable, no al mejor. Un fallback con Claude detrás de un Ollama local inestable no te salvará durante una interrupción de la API. `[más_rápido/mejor_calidad, calidad_fallback, siempre_local]` es un patrón común."

#: src/providers/fallback-and-routing.md:46
msgid "Routing — `router`"
msgstr "Enrutamiento — `router`"

#: src/providers/fallback-and-routing.md:48
msgid ""
"A `router` provider picks a backend per request based on hints supplied by "
"the caller."
msgstr "Un proveedor de `router` selecciona un backend por solicitud en función de las pistas proporcionadas por el llamador."

#: src/providers/fallback-and-routing.md:50
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[providers.models.brain]\n"
"kind = \"router\"\n"
"default = \"haiku\"                       # used if no hint matches\n"
"routes = [\n"
"    { hint = \"reasoning\", provider = \"deepseek-r1\" },\n"
"    { hint = \"cheap\",     provider = \"haiku\" },\n"
"    { hint = \"vision\",    provider = \"gemini\" },\n"
"]\n"
"```"
msgstr "```toml\n[providers.models.brain]\nkind = \"router\"\ndefault = \"haiku\"                       # se usa si no hay ninguna pista que coincida\nroutes = [\n    { hint = \"reasoning\", provider = \"deepseek-r1\" },\n    { hint = \"cheap\",     provider = \"haiku\" },\n    { hint = \"vision\",    provider = \"gemini\" },\n]\n```"

#: src/providers/fallback-and-routing.md:61
msgid ""
"Channels, tools, and SOPs can emit hints via request metadata. For example, "
"an SOP step might request `hint:reasoning` for a planning phase and `hint:"
"cheap` for a summarisation phase. Everything else goes to `default`."
msgstr "Los canales, herramientas y SOP pueden emitir pistas a través de los metadatos de la solicitud. Por ejemplo, un paso de SOP podría solicitar `hint:reasoning` para una fase de planificación y `hint:cheap` para una fase de resumen. Todo lo demás se envía a `default`."

#: src/providers/fallback-and-routing.md:63
msgid "Combining them"
msgstr "Combinándolos"

#: src/providers/fallback-and-routing.md:65
msgid ""
"`reliable` and `router` compose. Routes can point at `reliable` providers, "
"and `reliable` can wrap a `router`."
msgstr "`reliable` y `router` se componen. Las rutas pueden apuntar a proveedores `reliable`, y `reliable` puede envolver un `router`."

#: src/providers/fallback-and-routing.md:67
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[providers.models.production]\n"
"kind = \"reliable\"\n"
"fallback_providers = [\"brain\", \"local\"]  # if routing fails, fall to "
"local Ollama\n"
"\n"
"[providers.models.brain]\n"
"kind = \"router\"\n"
"default = \"haiku\"\n"
"routes = [\n"
"    { hint = \"reasoning\", provider = \"sonnet\" },\n"
"    { hint = \"cheap\",     provider = \"haiku\" },\n"
"]\n"
"```"
msgstr "```toml\n[providers.models.production]\nkind = \"reliable\"\nfallback_providers = [\"brain\", \"local\"]  # si el enrutamiento falla, recurrir a Ollama local\n\n[providers.models.brain]\nkind = \"router\"\ndefault = \"haiku\"\nroutes = [\n    { hint = \"reasoning\", provider = \"sonnet\" },\n    { hint = \"cheap\",     provider = \"haiku\" },\n]\n```"

#: src/providers/fallback-and-routing.md:81
msgid "Cost, performance, and reliability"
msgstr "Costo, rendimiento y fiabilidad"

