"[channels.dingtalk]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"app_key = \"...\"\n"
"app_secret = \"...\"\n"
"robot_code = \"...\"\n"
"```"
msgstr "```toml\n[channels.dingtalk]\nenabled = true\napp_key = \"...\"\napp_secret = \"...\"\nrobot_code = \"...\"\n```"

#: src/channels/chat-others.md:94
msgid "Alibaba's enterprise messenger. Same bot shape as WeCom."
msgstr "El mensajero empresarial de Alibaba. Misma forma de bot que WeCom."

#: src/channels/chat-others.md:96
msgid "Lark / Feishu"
msgstr "Lark / Feishu"

#: src/channels/chat-others.md:98
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.lark]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"app_id = \"...\"\n"
"app_secret = \"...\"\n"
"```"
msgstr "```toml\n[channels.lark]\nenabled = true\napp_id = \"...\"\napp_secret = \"...\"\n```"

#: src/channels/chat-others.md:105
msgid "QQ"
msgstr "No se puede traducir \"QQ\" ya que es un nombre propio o un término específico que no tiene una traducción directa al español. Si necesitas más contexto o una traducción específica, por favor proporciona más detalles."

#: src/channels/chat-others.md:107
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.qq]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"bot_id = \"...\"\n"
"bot_token = \"...\"\n"
"```"
msgstr "```toml\n[channels.qq]\nenabled = true\nbot_id = \"...\"\nbot_token = \"...\"\n```"

#: src/channels/chat-others.md:114
msgid ""
"Tencent's consumer messenger. Bot API access requires developer registration."
msgstr "El mensajero de consumo de Tencent. El acceso a la API de bot requiere registro de desarrollador."

#: src/channels/chat-others.md:116
msgid "IRC"
msgstr "IRC"

#: src/channels/chat-others.md:118
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.irc]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"server = \"irc.libera.chat\"\n"
"port = 6697\n"
"tls = true\n"
"nickname = \"zeroclaw\"\n"
"channels = [\"#mychannel\"]\n"
"nickserv_password = \"...\"          # optional\n"
"```"
msgstr "```toml\n[channels.irc]\nenabled = true\nserver = \"irc.libera.chat\"\nport = 6697\ntls = true\nnickname = \"zeroclaw\"\nchannels = [\"#mychannel\"]\nnickserv_password = \"...\"          # opcional\n```"

#: src/channels/chat-others.md:129
msgid "Classic IRC. Supports SASL, NickServ auth, and multiple channels."
msgstr "IRC clásico. Admite SASL, autenticación con NickServ y múltiples canales."

#: src/channels/chat-others.md:131
msgid "Mochat"
msgstr "Mochat"

#: src/channels/chat-others.md:133
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.mochat]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"api_key = \"...\"\n"
"# additional provider-specific fields\n"
"```"
msgstr "```toml\n[channels.mochat]\nenabled = true\napi_key = \"...\"\n# campos adicionales específicos del proveedor\n```"

#: src/channels/chat-others.md:140
msgid "Notion"
msgstr "Notion"

#: src/channels/chat-others.md:142
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.notion]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"integration_token = \"...\"\n"
"databases = [\"...\"]                # DB IDs the agent can write to\n"
"```"
msgstr "```toml\n[channels.notion]\nenabled = true\nintegration_token = \"...\"\ndatabases = [\"...\"]                # IDs de las bases de datos a las que el agente puede escribir\n```"

#: src/channels/chat-others.md:149
msgid ""
"Treats a Notion database as a message surface. Useful for asynchronous "
"workflows where the \"channel\" is a task inbox."
msgstr "Trata una base de datos de Notion como una superficie de mensajes. Útil para flujos de trabajo asíncronos donde el \"canal\" es una bandeja de tareas."

#: src/channels/chat-others.md:153
msgid "When to prefer a dedicated guide"
msgstr "Cuándo preferir una guía dedicada"

#: src/channels/chat-others.md:155
msgid ""
"Channels with more intricate setup (OAuth flows, end-to-end encryption, "
"multi-device considerations) live in their own pages:"
msgstr "Los canales con una configuración más compleja (flujos de OAuth, cifrado de extremo a extremo, consideraciones de múltiples dispositivos) se encuentran en sus propias páginas:"

#: src/channels/chat-others.md:157
msgid ""
"[Matrix](./matrix.md) — E2EE, device verification, Synapse/Dendrite specifics"
msgstr "[Matrix](./matrix.md) — E2EE, verificación de dispositivos, especificidades de Synapse/Dendrite"

#: src/channels/chat-others.md:162
msgid ""
"If you run into configuration friction on any channel above, file an issue "
"with the repro and we'll consider promoting it to a dedicated guide."
msgstr "Si encuentras algún problema de configuración en cualquiera de los canales mencionados, abre un problema con el ejemplo reproducible y consideraremos convertirlo en una guía dedicada."

#: src/channels/social.md:1
msgid "Social Channels"
msgstr "Canales sociales"

#: src/channels/social.md:3
msgid ""
"Broadcast / social-feed integrations. These differ from chat channels in two "
"ways: messages are typically public, and the agent often acts as a poster "
"rather than a bidirectional responder."
msgstr "Integraciones de difusión / redes sociales. Estas difieren de los canales de chat en dos aspectos: los mensajes suelen ser públicos y el agente a menudo actúa como publicador en lugar de un respondedor bidireccional."

#: src/channels/social.md:5
msgid "Bluesky (AT Protocol)"
msgstr "Bluesky (Protocolo AT)"

#: src/channels/social.md:7
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.bluesky]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"handle = \"you.bsky.social\"\n"
"app_password = \"xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx\"      # create at bsky.app/settings/"
"app-passwords\n"
"allowed_mentions = [\"@trustedfriend.bsky.social\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr "```toml\n[channels.bluesky]\nenabled = true\nhandle = \"you.bsky.social\"\napp_password = \"xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx\"      # crear en bsky.app/settings/app-passwords\nallowed_mentions = [\"@trustedfriend.bsky.social\"]\n```"

#: src/channels/social.md:15
msgid ""
"**Auth:** Bluesky app-password (not your real password). Create one in "
"settings."
msgstr "**Autenticación:** Contraseña de aplicación de Bluesky (no tu contraseña real). Crea una en la configuración."

#: src/channels/social.md:16
msgid ""
"**Inbound:** mentions and direct messages trigger the agent. Scope with "
"`allowed_mentions`."
msgstr "**Entrada:** las menciones y los mensajes directos activan el agente. Se delimita el alcance con `allowed_mentions`."

#: src/channels/social.md:17
msgid "**Outbound:** 300-character posts; longer responses auto-thread."
msgstr "**Saliente:** publicaciones de 300 caracteres; las respuestas más largas se dividen automáticamente en hilos."

#: src/channels/social.md:18
msgid "**Protocol:** AT Protocol via `atrium-api` crate."
msgstr "**Protocol:** Protocol AT a través del crate `atrium-api`."

#: src/channels/social.md:22
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.nostr]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"private_key_hex = \"...\"                   # nsec in hex\n"
"relays = [\n"
"    \"wss://relay.damus.io\",\n"
"    \"wss://nos.lol\",\n"
"    \"wss://relay.primal.net\",\n"
"]\n"
"allowed_pubkeys = [\"npub1...\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr "```toml\n[channels.nostr]\nenabled = true\nprivate_key_hex = \"...\"                   # nsec en hexadecimal\nrelays = [\n    \"wss://relay.damus.io\",\n    \"wss://nos.lol\",\n    \"wss://relay.primal.net\",\n]\nallowed_pubkeys = [\"npub1...\"]\n```"

#: src/channels/social.md:34
msgid ""
"**Auth:** raw private key. Store in the encrypted secrets backend — never in "
"a checked-in config."
msgstr "**Auth:** clave privada sin cifrar. Almacénala en el backend de secretos cifrado — nunca en una configuración incluida en el control de versiones."

#: src/channels/social.md:35
msgid ""
"**Inbound:** kind-1 (text), kind-4 (DM, NIP-04), and kind-1059 (gift-wrap, "
"NIP-17)."
msgstr "**Entrante:** kind-1 (texto), kind-4 (DM, NIP-04) y kind-1059 (gift-wrap, NIP-17)."

#: src/channels/social.md:36
msgid "**Outbound:** same kinds. Zap handling is experimental."
msgstr "**Saliente:** mismos tipos. El manejo de Zap es experimental."

#: src/channels/social.md:37
msgid ""
"**Relays:** the agent connects to all listed relays; use 3–5 for reliability."
msgstr "**Relays:** el agente se conecta a todos los relays enumerados; utiliza 3–5 para garantizar la fiabilidad."

#: src/channels/social.md:41
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.twitter]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"api_key = \"...\"\n"
"api_secret = \"...\"\n"
"access_token = \"...\"\n"
"access_secret = \"...\"\n"
"bearer_token = \"...\"\n"
"```"
msgstr "```toml\n[channels.twitter]\nenabled = true\napi_key = \"...\"\napi_secret = \"...\"\naccess_token = \"...\"\naccess_secret = \"...\"\nbearer_token = \"...\"\n```"

#: src/channels/social.md:51
msgid ""
"**Auth:** OAuth 1.0a app credentials. Requires Twitter Developer Portal "
"access — paid tier for full API v2 access."
msgstr "**Autenticación:** Credenciales de la aplicación OAuth 1.0a. Requiere acceso al Portal de Desarrolladores de Twitter — nivel de pago para acceso completo a la API v2."

#: src/channels/social.md:52
msgid "**Inbound:** mentions via the Filtered Stream endpoint."
msgstr "**Entrante:** menciones a través del punto final de la secuencia filtrada."

#: src/channels/social.md:53
msgid "**Outbound:** posts, replies, threads."
msgstr "**Saliente:** publicaciones, respuestas, hilos."

#: src/channels/social.md:54
msgid ""
"**Caveat:** the free tier is rate-limited to the point of near-uselessness. "
"Budget accordingly."
msgstr "**Aviso:** la capa gratuita está limitada por tasa hasta el punto de ser casi inútil. Presupueste en consecuencia."

#: src/channels/social.md:58
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.reddit]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"client_id = \"...\"\n"
"client_secret = \"...\"\n"
"username = \"...\"\n"
"password = \"...\"                          # or use refresh_token\n"
"user_agent = \"zeroclaw-agent/0.1 by your-username\"\n"
"subreddits = [\"rust\", \"commandline\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr "```toml\n[channels.reddit]\nenabled = true\nclient_id = \"...\"\nclient_secret = \"...\"\nusername = \"...\"\npassword = \"...\"                          # o usa refresh_token\nuser_agent = \"zeroclaw-agent/0.1 by your-username\"\nsubreddits = [\"rust\", \"commandline\"]\n```"

#: src/channels/social.md:69
msgid ""
"**Auth:** OAuth 2.0 password flow or refresh token. Password flow requires a "
"script-type app."
msgstr "**Autenticación:** Flujo de contraseña OAuth 2.0 o token de actualización. El flujo de contraseña requiere una aplicación de tipo script."

#: src/channels/social.md:70
msgid ""
"**Inbound:** new posts and comments in the configured subreddits, plus "
"replies to the agent's own posts."
msgstr "**Entrada:** nuevas publicaciones y comentarios en los subreddits configurados, además de respuestas a las publicaciones del agente."

#: src/channels/social.md:71
msgid "**Outbound:** posts, comments, private messages."
msgstr "**Saliente:** publicaciones, comentarios, mensajes privados."

#: src/channels/social.md:72
msgid ""
"**User-agent convention:** Reddit's API requires a descriptive user-agent "
"string. Non-compliance → rate limits."
msgstr "**Convención del agente de usuario:** La API de Reddit requiere una cadena de agente de usuario descriptiva. El incumplimiento → límites de tasa."

#: src/channels/social.md:76
msgid "Operating social channels safely"
msgstr "Operar los canales sociales de forma segura"

#: src/channels/social.md:78
msgid ""
"Bots on public social networks attract adversarial input. Two precautions:"
msgstr "Los bots en redes sociales públicas atraen entradas adversarias. Dos precauciones:"

#: src/channels/social.md:80
msgid ""
"**Restrict who the agent will respond to.** Use `allowed_mentions` / "
"`allowed_pubkeys` / `allowed_users` to whitelist. The default empty-list "
"behaviour varies per channel — check each."
msgstr "**Restringir a quién responderá el agente.** Usa `allowed_mentions` / `allowed_pubkeys` / `allowed_users` para agregar a la lista blanca. El comportamiento predeterminado de la lista vacía varía según el canal; revisa cada uno."

#: src/channels/social.md:81
msgid ""
"**Keep autonomy level at `Supervised` or lower.** A public-facing agent in "
"`Full` autonomy is effectively a public shell. If you want to run public-"
"facing, disable shell tools for that channel:"
msgstr "**Mantén el nivel de autonomía en `Supervised` o inferior.** Un agente de acceso público en autonomía `Full` es efectivamente una shell pública. Si deseas ejecutar un agente de acceso público, desactiva las herramientas de shell para ese canal:"

#: src/channels/social.md:83
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.bluesky]\n"
"tools_allow = [\"http\", \"web_search\"]      # whitelist — no shell, no "
"file_write\n"
"```"
msgstr "```toml\n[channels.bluesky]\ntools_allow = [\"http\", \"web_search\"]      # lista blanca — sin shell, sin file_write\n```"

#: src/channels/social.md:88
msgid "Rate limits and backoff"
msgstr "Límites de tasa y retroceso"

#: src/channels/social.md:90
msgid ""
"All social channels are subject to aggressive rate limits. ZeroClaw's "
"outbound queue uses exponential backoff on 429 responses. If you hit "
"persistent rate-limiting, lower `draft_update_interval_ms` and check whether "
"you're accidentally editing messages (Bluesky does not support edits; others "
"have per-operation limits)."
msgstr "Todos los canales sociales están sujetos a límites de tasa agresivos. La cola de salida de ZeroClaw utiliza retroceso exponencial en las respuestas 429. Si experimentas limitación persistente de tasa, reduce `draft_update_interval_ms` y verifica si estás editando mensajes accidentalmente (Bluesky no admite ediciones; otros tienen límites por operación)."

#: src/channels/email.md:3
msgid ""
"Two email channels depending on how you want inbound messages delivered."
msgstr "Dos canales de correo electrónico dependiendo de cómo quieras que se entreguen los mensajes entrantes."

#: src/channels/email.md:5
msgid "IMAP + SMTP (`email_channel`)"
msgstr "IMAP + SMTP (`email_channel`)"

#: src/channels/email.md:7
msgid ""
"The general-purpose email channel. Polls IMAP for new messages, sends via "
"SMTP. Works with Gmail, Outlook, Fastmail, self-hosted Postfix, and anything "
"else that speaks IMAP/SMTP."
msgstr "El canal de correo electrónico de propósito general. Analiza IMAP en busca de nuevos mensajes y envía a través de SMTP. Funciona con Gmail, Outlook, Fastmail, Postfix autoalojado y cualquier otro servicio que utilice IMAP/SMTP."

#: src/channels/email.md:9
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.email]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"\n"
"[channels.email.imap]\n"
"host = \"imap.example.com\"\n"
"port = 993\n"
"username = \"you@example.com\"\n"
"password = \"...\"                 # or app-password for Gmail/iCloud\n"
"mailbox = \"INBOX\"\n"
"poll_interval_secs = 60\n"
"\n"
"[channels.email.smtp]\n"
"host = \"smtp.example.com\"\n"
"port = 587\n"
"username = \"you@example.com\"\n"
"password = \"...\"\n"
"\n"
"[channels.email.filter]\n"
"allowed_senders = [\"boss@example.com\", \"alerts@example.com\"]\n"
"subject_prefix = \"[agent]\"       # only respond to subjects starting with "
"this\n"
"```"
msgstr "```toml\n[channels.email]\nenabled = true\n\n[channels.email.imap]\nhost = \"imap.example.com\"\nport = 993\nusername = \"you@example.com\"\npassword = \"...\"                 # o contraseña de aplicación para Gmail/iCloud\nmailbox = \"INBOX\"\npoll_interval_secs = 60\n\n[channels.email.smtp]\nhost = \"smtp.example.com\"\nport = 587\nusername = \"you@example.com\"\npassword = \"...\"\n\n[channels.email.filter]\nallowed_senders = [\"boss@example.com\", \"alerts@example.com\"]\nsubject_prefix = \"[agent]\"       # solo responder a asuntos que comiencen con este prefijo\n```"

#: src/channels/email.md:32
msgid "Gmail gotchas"
msgstr "Trucos de Gmail"

#: src/channels/email.md:34
msgid ""
"**App passwords required** if 2FA is on. Regular account password is "
"rejected."
msgstr "**Se requieren contraseñas de aplicación** si la autenticación de dos factores (2FA) está activada. La contraseña regular de la cuenta será rechazada."

#: src/channels/email.md:35
msgid "**\"Less secure app access\" is gone** — app password is the only path."
msgstr "**El acceso de aplicaciones menos seguras** ha desaparecido; la contraseña de la aplicación es la única opción."

#: src/channels/email.md:36
msgid ""
"Consider the Gmail Push channel below for real-time delivery instead of "
"polling."
msgstr "Considera el canal de Gmail Push para la entrega en tiempo real en lugar de la consulta periódica."

#: src/channels/email.md:38
msgid "Outlook / Office 365"
msgstr "Outlook / Office 365"

#: src/channels/email.md:40
msgid "OAuth 2.0 is recommended over password auth:"
msgstr "Se recomienda OAuth 2.0 sobre la autenticación con contraseña:"

#: src/channels/email.md:42
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.email.imap]\n"
"host = \"outlook.office365.com\"\n"
"port = 993\n"
"username = \"you@example.com\"\n"
"oauth_token = \"...\"              # managed via `zeroclaw channel auth "
"email`\n"
"```"
msgstr "```toml\n[channels.email.imap]\nhost = \"outlook.office365.com\"\nport = 993\nusername = \"you@example.com\"\noauth_token = \"...\"              # gestionado mediante `zeroclaw channel auth email`\n```"

#: src/channels/email.md:50
msgid "Gmail Push (`gmail_push`)"
msgstr "Gmail Push (`gmail_push`)"

#: src/channels/email.md:52
msgid "Real-time delivery via Google Cloud Pub/Sub — no polling."
msgstr "Entrega en tiempo real a través de Google Cloud Pub/Sub, sin sondeo."

#: src/channels/email.md:54
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.gmail_push]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"account = \"you@gmail.com\"\n"
"client_secret_json = \"~/.zeroclaw/gmail-client-secret.json\"\n"
"pubsub_topic = \"projects/my-project/topics/gmail-inbox\"\n"
"pubsub_subscription = \"projects/my-project/subscriptions/zeroclaw-sub\"\n"
"allowed_senders = [\"boss@example.com\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr "```toml\n[channels.gmail_push]\nenabled = true\naccount = \"you@gmail.com\"\nclient_secret_json = \"~/.zeroclaw/gmail-client-secret.json\"\npubsub_topic = \"projects/my-project/topics/gmail-inbox\"\npubsub_subscription = \"projects/my-project/subscriptions/zeroclaw-sub\"\nallowed_senders = [\"boss@example.com\"]\n```"

#: src/channels/email.md:66
msgid "Create a Google Cloud project, enable Gmail API and Pub/Sub API"
msgstr "Crea un proyecto de Google Cloud, habilita la API de Gmail y la API de Pub/Sub"

#: src/channels/email.md:67
msgid "Create a Pub/Sub topic the Gmail service can publish to"
msgstr "Crea un tema de Pub/Sub al que el servicio de Gmail pueda publicar"

#: src/channels/email.md:68
msgid "Create a pull subscription on that topic for ZeroClaw"
msgstr "Crea una suscripción pull en ese tema para ZeroClaw"

#: src/channels/email.md:69
msgid "Create OAuth client credentials (desktop app type), download JSON"
msgstr "Crear credenciales de cliente OAuth (tipo aplicación de escritorio), descargar JSON"

#: src/channels/email.md:70
msgid ""
"On first run, `zeroclaw channel auth gmail-push` opens a browser for the "
"OAuth consent"
msgstr "En la primera ejecución, `zeroclaw channel auth gmail-push` abre un navegador para el consentimiento de OAuth"

#: src/channels/email.md:71
msgid "The agent watches the subscription for new-mail notifications"
msgstr "El agente observa la suscripción para recibir notificaciones de nuevos correos."

#: src/channels/email.md:73
msgid ""
"Outbound sends still go via SMTP — configure an `smtp` block in this channel "
"the same way as the IMAP+SMTP channel."
msgstr "Los envíos salientes aún se realizan a través de SMTP — configura un bloque `smtp` en este canal de la misma manera que en el canal IMAP+SMTP."

#: src/channels/email.md:77
msgid "Reply threading"
msgstr "Hilo de respuestas"

#: src/channels/email.md:79
msgid ""
"Both email channels thread replies using `In-Reply-To` and `References` "
"headers so conversations stay grouped in whatever client the sender uses."
msgstr "Ambos canales de correo electrónico agrupan las respuestas mediante los encabezados `In-Reply-To` y `References`, de modo que las conversaciones permanezcan agrupadas en el cliente que utilice el remitente."

#: src/channels/email.md:81
msgid "Attachment handling"
msgstr "Manejo de archivos adjuntos"

#: src/channels/email.md:83
msgid ""
"Inbound attachments are stored under `<workspace>/attachments/<conversation>/"
"`. The agent gets file paths in its context and can read them via the "
"`file_read` tool."
msgstr "Los archivos adjuntos entrantes se almacenan en `<workspace>/attachments/<conversation>/`. El agente obtiene las rutas de los archivos en su contexto y puede leerlos mediante la herramienta `file_read`."

#: src/channels/email.md:85
msgid ""
"Outbound attachments are not supported yet — the agent replies with links to "
"files in the workspace, and the user downloads via whatever tunnel the "
"workspace is exposed through."
msgstr "Los archivos adjuntos de salida aún no son compatibles: el agente responde con enlaces a archivos en el espacio de trabajo, y el usuario los descarga a través del túnel mediante el cual se expone el espacio de trabajo."

#: src/channels/email.md:87
msgid "Rate and volume limits"
msgstr "Límites de tasa y volumen"

#: src/channels/email.md:89
msgid "Email isn't optimised for conversational latency. Expect:"
msgstr "El correo electrónico no está optimizado para la latencia conversacional. Espera:"

#: src/channels/email.md:91
msgid ""
"IMAP poll latency: `poll_interval_secs` (default 60 s). Lower at the cost of "
"server load; some providers rate-limit aggressive polling."
msgstr "Latencia de la encuesta IMAP: `poll_interval_secs` (predeterminado 60 s). Reduzca a costa de la carga del servidor; algunos proveedores limitan las encuestas agresivas."

#: src/channels/email.md:92
msgid ""
"SMTP send: subject to your provider's daily-send quota (Gmail: 500/day for "
"free accounts, 2000/day for Workspace)."
msgstr "Envío SMTP: sujeto a la cuota diaria de envíos de tu proveedor (Gmail: 500/día para cuentas gratuitas, 2000/día para Workspace)."

#: src/channels/email.md:94 src/hardware/index.md:67
msgid "Safety"
msgstr "Seguridad"

#: src/channels/email.md:96
msgid ""
"Email has no auth at the protocol level beyond SMTP's envelope — anyone can "
"claim to be anyone. Always configure `allowed_senders` (strict list of "
"addresses) or `subject_prefix` (shared secret in the subject line) before "
"exposing the agent to an inbox that receives public mail."
msgstr "El correo electrónico no tiene autenticación a nivel de protocolo más allá del sobre de SMTP: cualquiera puede hacerse pasar por cualquier persona. Configura siempre `allowed_senders` (lista estricta de direcciones) o `subject_prefix` (secreto compartido en la línea de asunto) antes de exponer el agente a una bandeja de entrada que reciba correo público."

#: src/channels/voice.md:1
msgid "Voice & Telephony"
msgstr "Voz y telefonía"

#: src/channels/voice.md:3
msgid ""
"Real-time voice input and output. Four channels cover the matrix: inbound "
"calls, outbound speech synthesis, local microphone wake, and SIP-grade real-"
"time conversation."
msgstr "Entrada y salida de voz en tiempo real. Cuatro canales cubren la matriz: llamadas entrantes, síntesis de voz saliente, activación por micrófono local y conversación en tiempo real de grado SIP."

#: src/channels/voice.md:5
msgid "ClawdTalk (real-time SIP)"
msgstr "ClawdTalk (SIP en tiempo real)"

#: src/channels/voice.md:7
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.clawdtalk]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"telnyx_api_key = \"...\"\n"
"connection_id = \"...\"              # Telnyx SIP connection\n"
"model_provider = \"voice-brain\"     # references [providers.models.voice-"
"brain]\n"
"voice = \"Polly.Joanna-Neural\"      # Telnyx voice ID\n"
"```"
msgstr "```toml\n[channels.clawdtalk]\nenabled = true\ntelnyx_api_key = \"...\"\nconnection_id = \"...\"              # Conexión SIP de Telnyx\nmodel_provider = \"voice-brain\"     # hace referencia a [providers.models.voice-brain]\nvoice = \"Polly.Joanna-Neural\"      # ID de voz de Telnyx\n```"

#: src/channels/voice.md:16
msgid ""
"Full-duplex SIP voice powered by Telnyx. The agent talks over a real phone "
"call — inbound or outbound. Supports barge-in, mid-turn tool use, and "
"regional number provisioning."
msgstr "Voz SIP full-duplex impulsada por Telnyx. El agente habla durante una llamada telefónica real — entrante o saliente. Admite barge-in, uso de herramientas en medio de la conversación y aprovisionamiento de números regionales."

#: src/channels/voice.md:18
msgid ""
"**Pair with:** a `telnyx` provider for the brain (`crates/zeroclaw-providers/"
"src/telnyx.rs`) and ensure your Telnyx account has a SIP connection with the "
"correct webhook URL pointed at the ZeroClaw gateway."
msgstr "**Emparejar con:** un proveedor `telnyx` para el cerebro (`crates/zeroclaw-providers/src/telnyx.rs`) y asegúrese de que su cuenta de Telnyx tenga una conexión SIP con la URL de webhook correcta apuntando al gateway de ZeroClaw."

#: src/channels/voice.md:20
msgid "Voice Call (Twilio / Telnyx / Plivo)"
msgstr "Llamada de voz (Twilio / Telnyx / Plivo)"

#: src/channels/voice.md:22
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.voice_call]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"carrier = \"twilio\"                 # or \"telnyx\", \"plivo\"\n"
"account_sid = \"...\"\n"
"auth_token = \"...\"\n"
"from_number = \"+14155550123\"\n"
"stt_provider = \"whisper\"\n"
"tts_provider = \"elevenlabs\"\n"
"```"
msgstr "```toml\n[channels.voice_call]\nenabled = true\ncarrier = \"twilio\"                 # o \"telnyx\", \"plivo\"\naccount_sid = \"...\"\nauth_token = \"...\"\nfrom_number = \"+14155550123\"\nstt_provider = \"whisper\"\ntts_provider = \"elevenlabs\"\n```"

#: src/channels/voice.md:33
msgid ""
"Traditional carrier voice — the agent picks up, transcribes with STT, "
"replies with TTS. Higher latency than ClawdTalk but works with any regular "
"phone number and doesn't require SIP trunk provisioning."
msgstr "Voz tradicional de operador: el agente recibe la llamada, transcribe con STT y responde con TTS. Mayor latencia que ClawdTalk, pero funciona con cualquier número de teléfono convencional y no requiere la configuración de una troncal SIP."

#: src/channels/voice.md:35
msgid "Voice Wake (local wake-word)"
msgstr "Activación por voz (palabra de activación local)"

#: src/channels/voice.md:37
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.voice_wake]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"wake_phrase = \"hey claw\"\n"
"engine = \"porcupine\"               # or \"openwakeword\"\n"
"model_path = \"~/.zeroclaw/wake/hey-claw.ppn\"\n"
"audio_device = \"default\"\n"
"```"
msgstr "```toml\n[channels.voice_wake]\nenabled = true\nwake_phrase = \"hey claw\"\nengine = \"porcupine\"               # o \"openwakeword\"\nmodel_path = \"~/.zeroclaw/wake/hey-claw.ppn\"\naudio_device = \"default\"\n```"

#: src/channels/voice.md:46
msgid ""
"Runs locally, listens on the mic, triggers agent interaction when it hears "
"the wake phrase. Useful for:"
msgstr "Se ejecuta localmente, escucha por el micrófono y activa la interacción con el agente cuando escucha la frase de activación. Útil para:"

#: src/channels/voice.md:48
msgid "Physical voice assistants on SBCs"
msgstr "Asistentes de voz físicos en SBCs"

#: src/channels/voice.md:49
msgid "Desktop \"hotword → ask\" workflows"
msgstr "Flujos de trabajo de escritorio \"palabra clave → pregunta\""

#: src/channels/voice.md:50
msgid "Always-listening home-automation agents"
msgstr "Agentes de automatización del hogar con escucha constante"

#: src/channels/voice.md:52
msgid ""
"The agent doesn't send audio anywhere — wake detection is local. Only post-"
"wake speech goes through STT and reaches the LLM."
msgstr "El agente no envía audio a ningún lugar; la detección de activación es local. Solo el habla posterior a la activación se procesa mediante STT y llega al LLM."

#: src/channels/voice.md:54
msgid "TTS (outbound speech synthesis)"
msgstr "TTS (síntesis de voz saliente)"

#: src/channels/voice.md:56
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.tts]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"engine = \"piper\"                   # local, free\n"
"voice = \"en_US-lessac-medium\"\n"
"output_device = \"default\"\n"
"```"
msgstr "```toml\n[channels.tts]\nenabled = true\nengine = \"piper\"                   # local, free\nvoice = \"en_US-lessac-medium\"\noutput_device = \"default\"\n```"

#: src/channels/voice.md:64
msgid "Other engines:"
msgstr "Otros motores:"

#: src/channels/voice.md:66
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.tts]\n"
"engine = \"openai\"                  # TTS-1 or TTS-1-HD\n"
"voice = \"alloy\"\n"
"api_key = \"...\"\n"
"\n"
"[channels.tts]\n"
"engine = \"elevenlabs\"\n"
"voice_id = \"21m00Tcm4TlvDq8ikWAM\"\n"
"api_key = \"...\"\n"
"\n"
"[channels.tts]\n"
"engine = \"google-cloud\"\n"
"voice = \"en-US-Neural2-J\"\n"
"credentials_json = \"~/.zeroclaw/gcp.json\"\n"
"\n"
"[channels.tts]\n"
"engine = \"edge\"                    # Microsoft Edge TTS — free, online\n"
"voice = \"en-US-AndrewNeural\"\n"
"```"
msgstr "```toml\n[channels.tts]\nengine = \"openai\"                  # TTS-1 o TTS-1-HD\nvoice = \"alloy\"\napi_key = \"...\"\n\n[channels.tts]\nengine = \"elevenlabs\"\nvoice_id = \"21m00Tcm4TlvDq8ikWAM\"\napi_key = \"...\"\n\n[channels.tts]\nengine = \"google-cloud\"\nvoice = \"en-US-Neural2-J\"\ncredentials_json = \"~/.zeroclaw/gcp.json\"\n\n[channels.tts]\nengine = \"edge\"                    # Microsoft Edge TTS — gratuito, en línea\nvoice = \"en-US-AndrewNeural\"\n```"

#: src/channels/voice.md:87
msgid ""
"TTS is output-only — it's not a conversation channel; it's a speaker for "
"other channels' replies. Pair with `voice_wake` for a complete local voice "
"assistant."
msgstr "TTS es de solo salida: no es un canal de conversación, sino un altavoz para las respuestas de otros canales. Combínalo con `voice_wake` para tener un asistente de voz local completo."

