"See [Hardware → Android](../hardware/android-setup.md) for Android-specific "
"audio setup."
msgstr "Consulta [Hardware → Android](../hardware/android-setup.md) para la configuración de audio específica de Android."

#: src/channels/webhook.md:3
msgid ""
"A generic inbound HTTP channel. Any service that can POST a JSON payload "
"(GitHub, Linear, Sentry, Zapier, cron-job.org, your own scripts) can hand "
"work to the agent via a webhook URL."
msgstr "Un canal HTTP entrante genérico. Cualquier servicio que pueda enviar una carga útil JSON mediante POST (GitHub, Linear, Sentry, Zapier, cron-job.org, tus propios scripts) puede entregar trabajo al agente a través de una URL de webhook."

#: src/channels/webhook.md:5
msgid ""
"Webhooks live inside the gateway — if the gateway is running, webhooks are "
"reachable at `/webhook/<name>`."
msgstr "Los webhooks se encuentran dentro del gateway: si el gateway está en ejecución, los webhooks son accesibles en `/webhook/<name>`."

#: src/channels/webhook.md:9
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.webhooks.github-issues]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"secret = \"...\"                    # HMAC secret for signature "
"verification\n"
"dispatch_to = \"sop:triage-issue\"  # or a conversation ID, or a system "
"prompt\n"
"allow_list = [\"github.com\"]       # enforce source IP allowlist\n"
"\n"
"[channels.webhooks.grafana]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"secret = \"...\"\n"
"dispatch_to = \"cron:alert-handler\"\n"
"```"
msgstr "```toml\n[channels.webhooks.github-issues]\nenabled = true\nsecret = \"...\"                    # Secreto HMAC para la verificación de firma\ndispatch_to = \"sop:triage-issue\"  # o un ID de conversación, o un prompt del sistema\nallow_list = [\"github.com\"]       # aplicar lista de permitidos de IP de origen\n\n[channels.webhooks.grafana]\nenabled = true\nsecret = \"...\"\ndispatch_to = \"cron:alert-handler\"\n```"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:22
msgid "The `dispatch_to` field points the inbound event at one of:"
msgstr "El campo `dispatch_to` dirige el evento entrante hacia uno de:"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:24
msgid ""
"`sop:<name>` — runs a Standard Operating Procedure with the payload as input"
msgstr "`sop:<name>` — ejecuta un Procedimiento Operativo Estándar con la carga útil como entrada"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:25
msgid "`cron:<name>` — triggers a scheduled job off-schedule"
msgstr "`cron:<name>` — activa un trabajo programado fuera de horario"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:26
msgid ""
"`conversation:<id>` — appends to a named conversation (agent responds "
"normally)"
msgstr "`conversation:<id>` — agrega a una conversación con nombre (el agente responde normalmente)"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:27
msgid ""
"`system:<prompt>` — runs a one-shot agent call with the payload appended to "
"a system prompt"
msgstr "`system:<prompt>` — ejecuta una llamada de agente de un solo paso con la carga útil añadida a un prompt del sistema"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:31
msgid ""
"GitHub, Stripe, Slack, and most major sources sign webhooks with HMAC. Set "
"`secret` to the shared secret; the channel verifies `X-Hub-Signature-256` / "
"`X-Signature` / equivalent before dispatching."
msgstr "GitHub, Stripe, Slack y la mayoría de las fuentes principales firman los webhooks con HMAC. Establece `secret` con el secreto compartido; el canal verifica `X-Hub-Signature-256` / `X-Signature` / equivalente antes de despachar."

#: src/channels/webhook.md:33
msgid ""
"Sources without signing (open webhooks) should at minimum set `allow_list` "
"to restrict by source IP. A webhook URL with no auth and no IP allowlist is "
"an open ingress — don't."
msgstr "Las fuentes sin firmar (webhooks abiertos) deben establecer al menos `allow_list` para restringir por dirección IP de origen. Una URL de webhook sin autenticación ni lista de permitidos de IP es un ingreso abierto — no lo hagas."

#: src/channels/webhook.md:35
msgid "Shape of what the agent sees"
msgstr "Forma de lo que ve el agente"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:37
msgid ""
"By default the agent receives the raw JSON payload as a user message. For "
"structured sources, use `template`:"
msgstr "Por defecto, el agente recibe el payload JSON sin procesar como un mensaje de usuario. Para fuentes estructuradas, utiliza `template`:"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:39
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.webhooks.sentry]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"secret = \"...\"\n"
"dispatch_to = \"sop:investigate-error\"\n"
"template = \"\"\"\n"
"New Sentry alert:\n"
"Level: {{ payload.level }}\n"
"Title: {{ payload.title }}\n"
"URL: {{ payload.web_url }}\n"
"\n"
"Stack:\n"
"{{ payload.exception.values[0].stacktrace }}\n"
"\"\"\"\n"
"```"
msgstr "```toml\n[channels.webhooks.sentry]\nenabled = true\nsecret = \"...\"\ndispatch_to = \"sop:investigate-error\"\ntemplate = \"\"\"\nNueva alerta de Sentry:\nNivel: {{ payload.level }}\nTítulo: {{ payload.title }}\nURL: {{ payload.web_url }}\n\nPila de llamadas:\n{{ payload.exception.values[0].stacktrace }}\n\"\"\"\n```"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:55
msgid ""
"Templates use MiniJinja; `payload` is the full JSON body, plus `headers` and "
"`query` for URL params."
msgstr "Las plantillas utilizan MiniJinja; `payload` es el cuerpo JSON completo, además de `headers` y `query` para los parámetros de la URL."

#: src/channels/webhook.md:57
msgid "Replies"
msgstr "Respuestas"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:59
msgid ""
"Webhook channels default to one-shot: the agent handles the event, writes to "
"the receipts log, and returns 200. For webhook sources that wait for a reply "
"(interactive bots, slash commands), set `reply_mode`:"
msgstr "Los canales de webhook se configuran por defecto como de un solo uso: el agente maneja el evento, escribe en el registro de recibos y devuelve 200. Para fuentes de webhook que esperan una respuesta (bots interactivos, comandos slash), establece `reply_mode`:"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:61
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[channels.webhooks.slack-slash]\n"
"enabled = true\n"
"secret = \"...\"\n"
"reply_mode = \"inline-json\"        # respond to POST with {\"text\": \"..."
"\"}\n"
"template = \"{{ payload.text }}\"\n"
"```"
msgstr "```toml\n[channels.webhooks.slack-slash]\nenabled = true\nsecret = \"...\"\nreply_mode = \"inline-json\"        # responder a POST con {\"text\": \"...\"}\ntemplate = \"{{ payload.text }}\"\n```"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:69
msgid ""
"Supported reply modes: `status-only` (default, 200 OK), `inline-json`, "
"`inline-text`."
msgstr "Modos de respuesta admitidos: `status-only` (predeterminado, 200 OK), `inline-json`, `inline-text`."

#: src/channels/webhook.md:71
msgid "Public exposure"
msgstr "Exposición pública"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:73
msgid ""
"By default the gateway binds to localhost only. To expose webhooks publicly:"
msgstr "Por defecto, el gateway se vincula solo a localhost. Para exponer los webhooks públicamente:"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:75
msgid ""
"**Reverse proxy** — run nginx / Caddy / Traefik in front, terminate TLS, "
"proxy to localhost. See [Operations → Network deployment](../ops/network-"
"deployment.md)."
msgstr "**Proxy inverso** — ejecuta nginx / Caddy / Traefik por delante, termina TLS y reenvía las solicitudes a localhost. Consulta [Operaciones → Despliegue de red](../ops/network-deployment.md)."

#: src/channels/webhook.md:76
msgid ""
"**Tunnel** — configure `[tunnel] provider = \"ngrok\" | \"cloudflare\" | "
"\"tailscale\"` and restart the daemon. Tunnels start alongside the gateway."
msgstr "**Túnel** — configura `[tunnel] provider = \"ngrok\" | \"cloudflare\" | \"tailscale\"` y reinicia el daemon. Los túneles se inician junto con la puerta de enlace."

#: src/channels/webhook.md:77
msgid ""
"**Public bind** — set `ZEROCLAW_ALLOW_PUBLIC_BIND=1` and `[gateway] host = "
"\"0.0.0.0\"`. Not recommended without a firewall in front."
msgstr "**Enlace público** — establece `ZEROCLAW_ALLOW_PUBLIC_BIND=1` y `[gateway] host = \"0.0.0.0\"`. No se recomienda sin un firewall delante."

#: src/channels/webhook.md:79
msgid "Rate limiting"
msgstr "Limitación de tasa"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:81
msgid ""
"The webhook channel applies a per-webhook-name rate limit (default 10/s). "
"Override:"
msgstr "El canal webhook aplica un límite de tasa por nombre de webhook (10/s por defecto). Anulación:"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:88
msgid "Excess requests return 429."
msgstr "Las solicitudes excesivas devuelven 429."

#: src/channels/webhook.md:90
msgid "Code"
msgstr "Código"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:92
msgid ""
"Channel: `crates/zeroclaw-channels/src/webhook.rs` (plus gateway ingress in "
"`crates/zeroclaw-gateway/`)"
msgstr "Canal: `crates/zeroclaw-channels/src/webhook.rs` (más la entrada del gateway en `crates/zeroclaw-gateway/`)"

#: src/channels/webhook.md:93
msgid "Templates: `crates/zeroclaw-runtime/src/templating.rs`"
msgstr "Plantillas: `crates/zeroclaw-runtime/src/templating.rs`"

