"**Telegram no responde** — Verifica el bot_token, los allowed_users y que el "
"Uno Q tenga conexión a Internet (WiFi)."

#: src/hardware/arduino-uno-q-setup.md:188
msgid ""
"**Out of memory** — Keep features minimal (`--features hardware` for Uno Q); "
"consider `compact_context = true`."
msgstr ""
"**Sin memoria suficiente** — Mantén las características mínimas (`--features "
"hardware` para Uno Q); considera `compact_context = true`."

#: src/hardware/arduino-uno-q-setup.md:189
msgid ""
"**GPIO commands ignored** — Ensure Bridge app is running (`zeroclaw "
"peripheral setup-uno-q` deploys and starts it). Config must have `board = "
"\"arduino-uno-q\"` and `transport = \"bridge\"`."
msgstr ""
"**Comandos GPIO ignorados** — Asegúrate de que la aplicación Bridge esté en "
"ejecución (`zeroclaw peripheral setup-uno-q` la despliega y la inicia). La "
"configuración debe tener `board = \"arduino-uno-q\"` y `transport = \"bridge"
"\"`."

#: src/hardware/arduino-uno-q-setup.md:190
msgid ""
"**LLM provider (GLM/Zhipu)** — Use `default_provider = \"glm\"` or `\"zhipu"
"\"` with `GLM_API_KEY` in env or config. ZeroClaw uses the correct v4 "
"endpoint."
msgstr ""
"**Proveedor de LLM (GLM/Zhipu)** — Usa `default_provider = \"glm\"` o `"
"\"zhipu\"` con `GLM_API_KEY` en el entorno o configuración. ZeroClaw utiliza "
"el extremo correcto de la versión 4."

#: src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:1
msgid "ZeroClaw on Nucleo-F401RE — Step-by-Step Guide"
msgstr "ZeroClaw en Nucleo-F401RE — Guía paso a paso"

#: src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:3
msgid ""
"Run ZeroClaw on your Mac or Linux host. Connect a Nucleo-F401RE via USB. "
"Control GPIO (LED, pins) via Telegram or CLI."
msgstr ""
"Ejecuta ZeroClaw en tu host de Mac o Linux. Conecta un Nucleo-F401RE "
"mediante USB. Controla GPIO (LED, pines) a través de Telegram o CLI."

#: src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:7
msgid "Get Board Info via Telegram (No Firmware Needed)"
msgstr ""
"Obtener información de la placa a través de Telegram (sin necesidad de "
"firmware)"

#: src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:9
msgid ""
"ZeroClaw can read chip info from the Nucleo over USB **without flashing any "
"firmware**. Message your Telegram bot:"
msgstr ""
"ZeroClaw puede leer la información del chip desde el Nucleo a través de USB "
"**sin necesidad de cargar ningún firmware**. Envía un mensaje a tu bot de "
"Telegram:"

#: src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:11
msgid "_\"What board info do I have?\"_"
msgstr "\"¿Qué información de la placa tengo?\""

#: src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:12
msgid "_\"Board info\"_"
msgstr "\"Información de la placa\""

#: src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:13
msgid "_\"What hardware is connected?\"_"
msgstr "\"¿Qué hardware está conectado?\""

#: src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:14
msgid "_\"Chip info\"_"
msgstr "\"Información del chip\""

#: src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:16
msgid ""
"The agent uses the `hardware_board_info` tool to return chip name, "
"architecture, and memory map. With the `probe` feature, it reads live data "
"via USB/SWD; otherwise it returns static datasheet info."
msgstr ""
"El agente utiliza la herramienta `hardware_board_info` para devolver el "
"nombre del chip, la arquitectura y el mapa de memoria. Con la función "
"`probe`, lee datos en tiempo real a través de USB/SWD; de lo contrario, "
"devuelve información estática del datasheet."

#: src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:18
msgid ""
"**Config:** Run `zeroclaw onboard` (hardware step adds the board "
"interactively), or use `zeroclaw config set peripherals.boards.0.board "
"nucleo-f401re`, `transport serial`, and `path <your-serial-port>`. See the "
"[Config reference](../reference/config.md) for all fields."
msgstr "**Config:** Ejecute `zeroclaw onboard` (el paso de hardware agrega la placa de forma interactiva), o utilice `zeroclaw config set peripherals.boards.0.board nucleo-f401re`, `transport serial` y `path <your-serial-port>`. Consulte la [Referencia de configuración](../reference/config.md) para ver todos los campos."

#: src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:20
msgid "**CLI alternative:**"
msgstr "**Alternativa de CLI:**"

#: src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:32
msgid "ZeroClaw includes everything for Nucleo-F401RE:"
msgstr "ZeroClaw incluye todo lo necesario para Nucleo-F401RE:"

#: src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:36
msgid "Firmware"
msgstr "Firmware"

#: src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:36
msgid "`firmware/nucleo/`"
msgstr "`firmware/nucleo/`"

#: src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:36
msgid "Embassy Rust — USART2 (115200), gpio_read, gpio_write"
msgstr "Embassy Rust — USART2 (115200), gpio_read, gpio_write"

#: src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:37
msgid "Serial peripheral"
msgstr "Periférico serie"

#: src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:37
msgid "`crates/zeroclaw-hardware/src/peripherals/serial.rs`"
msgstr "`crates/zeroclaw-hardware/src/peripherals/serial.rs`"

#: src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:37
msgid "JSON-over-serial protocol (same as Arduino/ESP32)"
msgstr "Protocolo JSON sobre serie (igual que Arduino/ESP32)"

#: src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:38
msgid "Flash command"
msgstr "Comando de flash"

#: src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:38
msgid "Builds firmware, flashes via probe-rs"
msgstr "Compila el firmware y lo flashea mediante probe-rs"

#: src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:40
msgid ""
"Protocol: newline-delimited JSON. Request: `{\"id\":\"1\",\"cmd\":"
"\"gpio_write\",\"args\":{\"pin\":13,\"value\":1}}`. Response: `{\"id\":\"1\","
"\"ok\":true,\"result\":\"done\"}`."
msgstr ""
"Protocolo: JSON delimitado por saltos de línea. Solicitud: `{\"id\":\"1\","
"\"cmd\":\"gpio_write\",\"args\":{\"pin\":13,\"value\":1}}`. Respuesta: `{\"id"
"\":\"1\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":\"done\"}`."

#: src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:46
msgid "Nucleo-F401RE board"
msgstr "Placa Nucleo-F401RE"

#: src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:47
msgid "USB cable (USB-A to Mini-USB; Nucleo has built-in ST-Link)"
msgstr "Cable USB (USB-A a Mini-USB; Nucleo tiene ST-Link integrado)"

#: src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:48
msgid ""
"For flashing: `cargo install probe-rs-tools --locked` (or use the [install "
"script](https://probe.rs/docs/getting-started/installation/))"
msgstr ""
"Para flashear: `cargo install probe-rs-tools --locked` (o utiliza el [script "
"de instalación](https://probe.rs/docs/getting-started/installation/))"

#: src/hardware/nucleo-setup.md:52
